01:22:22,436 --> 01:22:26,270
That's very nice.
Spam and Reese's. All right.

1194
01:22:26,440 --> 01:22:28,840
I love Spam and Reese's.
Can I have it?

1195
01:22:28,943 --> 01:22:30,535
I guess.

1196
01:22:31,445 --> 01:22:33,538
- Doug!
- That's all right.

1197
01:22:33,573 --> 01:22:36,473
- I'm sorry.
- So...

1198
01:22:37,451 --> 01:22:38,713
...how's Lucy?

1199
01:22:39,453 --> 01:22:42,183
Actually, she's living at the institute.

1200
01:22:42,957 --> 01:22:46,324
- When did that happen?
- Three weeks ago.

1201
01:22:46,961 --> 01:22:50,692
Said she didn't want to be a burden to
me and Doug anymore. I don't know.

1202
01:22:50,965 --> 01:22:53,433
I couldn't talk her out of it.
You know what?

1203
01:22:53,467 --> 01:22:55,662
She's doing really great up there.

1204
01:22:55,970 --> 01:22:59,030
She's teaching an art class
and she gets to paint every day.

1205
01:22:59,473 --> 01:23:01,304
In fact, she's even singing again.

1206
01:23:01,475 --> 01:23:03,670
Hey, look, I got a little gift
for you too.

1207
01:23:03,978 --> 01:23:07,778
It's just a little something
from one sailor to another one.

1208
01:23:09,483 --> 01:23:11,417
You take care of yourself out there.

1209
01:23:11,986 --> 01:23:14,420
- I will.
- Okay.

1210
01:23:22,997 --> 01:23:24,931
Henry did not tell me about you.

1211
01:23:24,999 --> 01:23:27,593
Your fisherman muscles.

1212
01:23:28,502 --> 01:23:29,764
Can I touch?

1213
01:23:30,004 --> 01:23:31,835
Sure.

1214
01:23:37,511 --> 01:23:39,445
Yes.

1215
01:23:47,021 --> 01:23:48,318
The Beach Boys?

1216
01:23:48,522 --> 01:23:51,389
How nice of him to give me a CD
that will remind me...

1217
01:23:52,026 --> 01:23:55,484
...of all the wonderful times
I shared with his daughter.

1218
01:23:55,529 --> 01:23:57,929
What an asshole!

1219
01:24:16,550 --> 01:24:18,575
Oh, why?

1220
01:24:19,053 --> 01:24:21,385
Why would you do this to me?

1221
01:24:21,555 --> 01:24:24,080
You sick bastard!

1222
01:24:28,562 --> 01:24:30,120
Oh, my God.

1223
01:24:31,065 --> 01:24:32,999
Is he trying to tell me something?

1224
01:24:37,571 --> 01:24:40,005
She only sings on days
she meets you.

1225
01:24:42,076 --> 01:24:44,044
She remembers me?

1226
01:24:44,578 --> 01:24:46,170
Holy shit!

1227
01:24:47,581 --> 01:24:50,345
She remembers me!

1228
01:24:55,589 --> 01:24:57,506
Julia, that looks great.

1229
01:24:57,541 --> 01:24:59,423
Excuse me. What am I doing?

1230
01:25:00,094 --> 01:25:03,359
You're painting a picture.
And you're doing an excellent job.

1231
01:25:03,597 --> 01:25:05,224
Oh.

1232
01:25:06,600 --> 01:25:09,626
Holy crap! I suck.

1233
01:25:18,112 --> 01:25:19,807
Hey, hey, hey.

1234
01:25:20,114 --> 01:25:22,947
- Can we help you, sir?
- Yes. I have an appointment.

1235
01:25:23,117 --> 01:25:25,551
- What's your name?
- My name?

1236
01:25:28,122 --> 01:25:31,319
Dude, he forgot his name.
I feel bad for him.

1237
01:25:31,625 --> 01:25:34,526
Just go on up. And good luck
with that memory problem.

1238
01:25:34,628 --> 01:25:36,619
Yeah. Thank you.

1239
01:25:38,632 --> 01:25:39,929
What?

1240
01:25:40,634 --> 01:25:42,727
Lucy!

1241
01:25:43,137 --> 01:25:44,832
Lucy!

1242
01:25:45,139 --> 01:25:47,789
- Hi, I'm Tom.
- Hey, I met you before. I'm Henry.

1243
01:25:47,824 --> 01:25:50,439
Maybe you can help me.
I'm looking for Lucy Whitmore.

1244
01:25:50,644 --> 01:25:52,168
Any idea where I can find her?

1245
01:25:52,646 --> 01:25:53,612
Hi, I'm Tom.

1246
01:25:53,647 --> 01:25:56,616
Oh. Thanks anyways.

1247
01:25:57,651 --> 01:25:59,516
Lucy!

1248
01:26:00,154 --> 01:26:01,621
Lucy!

1249
01:26:05,659 --> 01:26:07,422
Lucy Whitmore...

1250
01:26:08,662 --> 01:26:10,527
...can I ask you a question?

1251
01:26:13,667 --> 01:26:15,862
Do you have any idea who I am?

1252
01:26:22,176 --> 01:26:25,339
- No.
- No?

1253
01:26:26,680 --> 01:26:28,705
That sucks.

1254
01:26:30,184 --> 01:26:33,176
- What's your name?
- I'm Henry.

1255
01:26:33,687 --> 01:26:35,450
Henry.

1256
01:26:36,690 --> 01:26:39,557
I want to show you something.
Will you come with me?

1257
01:26:40,194 --> 01:26:41,593
Well, yeah.

1258
01:26:43,197 --> 01:26:45,131
Hey. Do you know who that guy is?

1259
01:26:45,199 --> 01:26:47,360
Dude, I don't even know who I am.

1260
01:26:47,701 --> 01:26:49,965
Oh, well, you're Pablo Picasso.

1261
01:26:50,204 --> 01:26:53,901
- Really?
- No. Not really.

1262
01:26:57,211 --> 01:26:59,873
This is my studio.

1263
01:27:19,233 --> 01:27:21,895
I don't know who you are, Henry...

1264
01:27:23,737 --> 01:27:27,673
...but I dream about you
almost every night.

1265
01:27:30,244 --> 01:27:31,768
Why?

1266
01:27:32,246 --> 01:27:36,307
What would you say if I told you
that notebook you read every day...

1267
01:27:36,750 --> 01:27:39,776
...used to have a lot of stuff
about me in it?

1268
01:27:41,255 --> 01:27:43,849
I would say that that
makes a lot of sense.

1269
01:27:44,258 --> 01:27:46,055
You erased me
from your memories...

1270
01:27:46,260 --> 01:27:49,423
...because you thought you were
holding me back from having...

1271
01:27:49,763 --> 01:27:51,492
...a full and happy life.

1272
01:27:51,765 --> 01:27:54,256
But you made a mistake.

1273
01:27:54,768 --> 01:27:58,397
Being with you is the only way
I could have a full and happy life.

1274
01:27:59,273 --> 01:28:01,537
You're the girl of my dreams...

1275
01:28:01,775 --> 01:28:05,541
...and apparently I'm the man of yours.

1276
01:28:10,284 --> 01:28:12,047
Henry.

1277
01:28:12,286 --> 01:28:13,685
It's nice to meet you.

1278
01:28:14,288 --> 01:28:17,280
Lucy, it's nice to meet you too.

1279
01:28:21,795 --> 01:28:23,763
Hi, I'm Tom.

1280
01:28:23,797 --> 01:28:25,958
Henry, Lucy. Nice to meet you, Tom.

1281
01:28:26,300 --> 01:28:29,929
Now why don't you come back in
ten seconds so we can meet again?

1282
01:29:15,349 --> 01:29:18,944
Do you, Honah Lee, take this woman
to be your lawfully wedded wife...

1283
01:29:18,979 --> 01:29:21,218
...to have and to hold
from this day forth...

1284
01:29:21,855 --> 01:29:23,948
...as long as you both shall live?

1285
01:29:23,983 --> 01:29:25,825
- I do.
- Really?

1286
01:29:26,360 --> 01:29:28,555
Even though in, like, 10, 15 years...

1287
01:29:28,862 --> 01:29:31,558
...she could possibly let herself
go and then, like...

1288
01:29:31,593 --> 01:29:33,731
...sex could be, like,
nauseating for you?

1289
01:29:33,867 --> 01:29:36,563
What are you, nuts?
Your wife's right over there.

1290
01:29:38,872 --> 01:29:40,601
I'm just kidding, Muumuu!

1291
01:29:40,874 --> 01:29:43,741
I now pronounce you man and wife.

1292
01:29:48,882 --> 01:29:51,350
Mazel tov!

1293
01:29:52,386 --> 01:29:54,479
It's very cold, so when you're ready...

1294
01:29:54,888 --> 01:29:58,517
...put on a jacket and come have
breakfast with me. Love you.

1295
01:30:30,424 --> 01:30:35,521
Hey, hey! Good morning, Mrs. Roth.
Would you like to meet your daughter?

1296
01:30:35,929 --> 01:30:37,191
Go say hello to Mommy.

1297
01:30:38,932 --> 01:30:40,593
Hi, Mommy.

1298
01:30:42,936 --> 01:30:44,927
That's right.

1299
01:30:46,440 --> 01:30:48,067
Good morning.

1300
01:30:49,943 --> 01:30:52,104
Oh, my goodness!

1301
01:30:52,946 --> 01:30:55,278
- Grandpa's here.
- Hi, Dad.

